The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Second season from April 10
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Second season from April 10
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Lalit Modi, IPL chairman and commissioner, on Tuesday announced that the second season of the IPL would start tentatively from April 10, 2009 and continue till May 29, according to a release.         
	Modi also announced that the format would remain the same as that of the inaugural season.         
	The eight franchises will play against one another on a home and away basis.         
	The top four will then figure in the two semi-finals and the winners of the semi-finals will clash in the final.         
	Modi said: The dates were decided at a meeting of the governing council in Mumbai.                                                                                                                          
